Description: Lightweight S-style guitar, weighing in at 7 pounds, 2 ounces. Charcoal Frost finish with tortoise guard, which looks great. The stock EBMM pickups sound terrific and it's the quietest guitar I've ever played thanks to the on-board wide spectrum silent circuit, which takes a 9-volt battery to power. (See pics of the back and you'll notice the battery compartment.) Straight-pull oversized headstock means no string trees. Locking tuners stabilize the guitar overall, especially when using the whammy bar. Active electronics for hum-free performance. Stainless steel frets will last for years. Compensated nut maintains superior intonation. Truly all the features you'd want in a high-end S-style axe. I set it up to play with 10-52 gauge strings. All hardware is stock. A previous owner moved the strap button to the back, but it is back in its regular spot - see the pics. Has light swirls and wear consistent with a used guitar. In excellent shape overall, and the reflect the condition. Will ship to continental USA via UPS Ground.
